svg.title: Present weather reported from a manned weather station: Blowing spray at the station, in the case of ships
svg.desc: WMO international weather symbol: No precipitation at the station at the time of observation: No precipitation, fog, ice fog, duststorm, sandstorm, drifting or blowing snow at the station* at the time of observation or during the preceding hour. *The expression “at the station” refers to a land station or a ship: Haze, dust, sand or smoke: Present weather reported from a manned weather station: Blowing spray at the station, in the case of ships
